  <abstract>A man, woman, and three children barter for goods at the Butler and Householder Rolling Store. The woman holds a chicken in her hand. Above the cab of the truck sits a chicken coop.</abstract>
  <abstract>A Depression-era throwback to the barter economy, "rolling stores" allowed country housewives to trade eggs and chickens for groceries.</abstract>
